keyPoints:
Version 1 (prone to false sharing):
#pragma omp parallel for
for (int i = 0; i < N; i++)
 sum += a[i];
Without reduction, all threads write to shared 'sum', causing severe false sharing on the variable itself

Version 2 (optimized with reduction):
#pragma omp parallel for reduction(+:sum)
for (int i = 0; i < N; i++)
 sum += a[i];
Creates private copies per thread, eliminates coherence traffic during loop

Version 3 (thread-local with manual combine):
#pragma omp parallel
{
 double local_sum = 0;
 #pragma omp for
 for (int i = 0; i < N; i++)
 local_sum += a[i];
 #pragma omp atomic
 sum += local_sum;
}
Uses atomic for final combine—less contention than each iteration
